    question: "Your research coordinator receives results from 8 subagents. Six succeeded completely, one returned partial results (3 of 5 data sources queried before timeout), and one failed entirely (authentication error). The user needs the report urgently. What should the coordinator do?",
    choices: { A: "Ask the user whether they want a partial or complete report", B: "Produce the report using only the 6 fully successful subagents, omitting the other two topics entirely", C: "Retry both failed subagents and wait for complete results before producing the report", D: "Produce the report using all available data, clearly annotating which sections are fully supported, which are based on partial data, and which topics have no coverage due to the authentication failure" },
